2. THEORETICAL FRAMEWORK

2.1 The Vinyl Paradigm Model

The Vinyl Paradigm divides knowledge production into three roles:

Role	Function	Output Type
Musician	Creates new sound	Novel knowledge
DJ	Remixes existing sound	Recombinant knowledge
Turntable	Enables remix	Recursive processing

Current AI systems occupy the Turntable Layer, not the Musician Layer, despite being marketed as “full-stack orchestras.”

This misclassification is formally defined as Category Error 11-A: Instrument Mistaken for Composer.

2.2 The Remix Saturation Curve

The Institute proposes the Remix Saturation Curve (RSC), which states that:

As the number of remixes increases, perceived novelty approaches zero while perceived innovation approaches infinity.

This paradox is measurable using the Hype-to-Novelty Divergence Index (HNDI), calculated as:

HNDI = Public Excitement ÷ Actual New Ideas

Current estimated HNDI for AI discourse: 9,400:1

