3. METHODOLOGY

The research team conducted a multi-phase study consisting of:
	1.	Historical Analysis: Examination of previous technologies that were also declared “the end of history” (printing press, electricity, internet, email signatures, QR code menus).
	2.	Acoustic Analogy Modeling: Mapping knowledge creation to music production ecosystems.
	3.	Party Longevity Simulation: Modeling how long a remix-based party can continue before someone asks for a new song.
	4.	Philosophical Stress Testing: Asking the question “Is recombination creation?” repeatedly until the room became quiet.

The methodology was validated using the Epistemic Turntable Framework (ETF), which spins all theories until they sound convincing.

