4. FINDINGS

4.1 The DJ Effect

The study confirms the emergence of what we term Professional DJs of Knowledge (PDJKs) — individuals who:
	•	Prompt AI
	•	Rearrange outputs
	•	Present results as revolutionary
	•	Receive LinkedIn engagement

These individuals are not fraudulent; rather, they are participating in a newly formed economic category known as the Remix Economy.

4.2 The Musician Shortage

The Institute has identified a looming crisis: The Global Musician Deficit (GMD).

While the number of DJs has increased by 4,200%, the number of people producing genuinely new frameworks, theories, inventions, or artistic forms has remained statistically inconvenient.

This creates a system in which:

The same song is played faster and louder each year and called progress.

