7. CONCLUSION

This paper concludes that Artificial Intelligence is simultaneously:
	•	Overestimated in its creativity
	•	Underestimated in its utility
	•	Misunderstood in its role
	•	Inevitable
	•	Overhyped
	•	Transformative
	•	Not transformative
	•	The future
	•	A tool
	•	The same song
	•	A new genre

The Institute therefore recommends immediate continued excitement, cautious skepticism, large investments, philosophical restraint, widespread adoption, and mild doubt.

In summary:
The party will neither end nor continue.
The music will both change and remain the same.
The DJs will become musicians, except when they don’t.
The turntable will be blamed regardless.

